It has long been speculated that Chester Bennington (Linkin Park), Chris Cornell (Soundgarden), and Anthony Bourdain didn’t commit suicide.  There are many suspicious circumstances dealing with their deaths that indicate that they were possibly murdered.  Now this is purely speculation (at this point), but mystery still surrounds their deaths.  Besides being engulfed in fame and fortune, they also had something else in common: they were all investigating elite pedophile sex rings.  We discuss a Twitter thread by @9kwiz that breaks down the suspicious ties surrounding Bennington and Cornell.  Watch until the end because we make another interesting discovery!
